		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There does not appear to be an MMC2 dumper plugin. As a CopyNES owner, you have two choices:
<br />
<br />1. Write the plugin yourself.
<br />2. Let somebody else write the plugin and give you a copy of it.
<br />
<br />If you know 6502 assembly, #1 shouldn't be too difficult - just start with a dumper for a different mapper (like MMC3) and modify it to use the MMC2 registers instead. Otherwise, I'm sure somebody else here can figure out how to do it - I'd write it myself, except that I have neither a CopyNES (yet - though it's on its way to kevtris right now) nor a Punch-Out cartridge to test it with.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

