	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Specifically, with source we could generalize this to cover MMC4 (<em>Famicom Wars</em>; <em>Fire Emblem</em>) as well, but then we might need an extra feature to dump MMC4's battery backed SRAM.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Quietust</b> [ Thu Dec 01, 2005 10:46 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />An MMC2 dumper would not be compatible with the MMC4, since they use different bank sizes (MMC2 uses 8KB at $8000-$9FFF with $A000-$FFFF containing the last 24KB, while MMC4 uses 16KB at $8000-$BFFF with $C000-$FFFF containing the last 16KB). The best we could do is to create a new plugin to handle MMC4.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


